"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-boxing-2024-0304-1435984-gallagher-and-cassidy-march-on-at-olympic-qualifiers\", \"text\": \"Two more Irish boxers progressed at the the Olympic qualifiers in Italy on Monday.  On Sunday,Martin McDonagh and Daina Moorehousegot the job done, and they were joined by Jude Gallagher and Kelyn Cassidy at the E-Work Arena in Busto Arsizio.  Tyrone feathwerweight Gallagher had too much for Algerian Hichem Maouche, pevailing on a unanimous decision. Gallagher is up again on Friday against India's Husam Mohammed.  Waterford man Cassidy got the better of Greek opponent Michail Tsamalidis by a unanimous decision in their light heavyweight tussle to make the last 32, where he will take on Guatemala's Wyatt Trujillo.  There was disappointment however for Jenny Lehane who lost on a split decision against France's Romane Moulai.  All fighters will seal a ticket to the Paris Games if they make it as far as the semi-finals.  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"